Detailed Description

Definition of the Smart Energy Tunneling (Complex Metering) Cluster.

Microchip Corporation: http://www.microchip.com

Definition in file zclSmartEnergyTunnelCluster.h.

Define Documentation

#define ZCL_SE_ERROR_TUNNEL_ID   0xFFFF

The Smart Energy Tunneling Cluster provides an interface for tunneling protocols. It is comprised of commands and attributes required to transport any existing metering communication protocol within the payload of standard ZigBee frames (including the handling of issues such as addressing, fragmentation and flow control). Examples for such protocols are DLMS/COSEM, IEC61107, ANSI C12, M-Bus, ClimateTalk etc. See ZigBee Smart Energy Profile Specification r17, D.6, page 268. In case of unseccussful tunnel opening tunnelId should have value 0xFFFF in RequestTunnelResponse command. ZigBee Smart Energy Profile Specification r17, D.6.2.5.1.2, page 284.

Definition at line 43 of file zclSmartEnergyTunnelCluster.h.

#define ZCL_SE_TUNNEL_CLUSTER_CLIENT_COMMANDS_AMOUNT   7

Total number of the SE Tunnel Cluster commands sent by the server. The number includes mandatory commands:

  • RequestTunnelResponse, TransferData, TransferDataError and optional commands:
  • AckTransferData, ReadyData, Supported Tunnel Protocols Response, and TunnelClosureNotification. See ZigBee Smart Energy Profile Specification r17, Table D.65, page 283.

Definition at line 54 of file zclSmartEnergyTunnelCluster.h.

#define REQUEST_TUNNEL_RESPONSE_COMMAND_ID   0x00

Command identifiers that are generated by the server. See ZigBee Smart Energy Profile Specification r17, Table D.65.

The command is sent by the server in response to a RequestTunnel command previously received from the client.

Definition at line 60 of file zclSmartEnergyTunnelCluster.h.

#define TRANSFER_DATA_CLIENT_COMMAND_ID   0x01

Command that transfers data from server to the client.

#define TRANSFER_DATA_ERROR_CLIENT_COMMAND_ID   0x02

This command is generated by the receiver of a TransferData command if the tunnel status indicates that something is wrong..

Definition at line 65 of file zclSmartEnergyTunnelCluster.h.

#define ACK_TRANSFER_DATA_CLIENT_COMMAND_ID   0x03

The command is confirmation of a DataTransfer command.

Definition at line 67 of file zclSmartEnergyTunnelCluster.h.

#define READY_DATA_CLIENT_COMMAND_ID   0x04

The command is generated after a receiver had to stop the dataflow using the AckTransferData(0) command to indicate that the device is now ready to continue receiving data.

Definition at line 71 of file zclSmartEnergyTunnelCluster.h.

#define SUPPORTED_TUNNEL_PROTOCOLS_RESPONSE_COMMAND_ID   0x05

Supported Tunnel Protocols Response is sent in response to a Get Supported Tunnel Protocols command previously received. The response contains a list of tunnel protocols supported by the device.

Definition at line 75 of file zclSmartEnergyTunnelCluster.h.

#define TUNNEL_CLOSURE_NOTIFICATION_COMMAND_ID   0x06

The command is sent by the server to indicate that a tunnel has been closed due to expiration of a CloseTunnelTimeout.

Macro defines the ZCL SE Tunnel Cluster on client side.

Note:
The client has no attributes. See ZSE Profile Spec. r17, D.6.3.2.
Parameters:
[in]clcommands- pointer to commands of the SE Tunneling Cluster on client and server side.
See also:
ZCL_SeTunnelCommands_t.
Returns:
None.

Total number of cluster-specific commands sent by the server. Mandatory commands:

Typedef Documentation

typedef BEGIN_PACK struct _ZclRequestTunnelPayload_t ZclRequestTunnelPayload_t

The request payload specifies the protocol identifier for the requested tunnel, a manufacturer code in case of proprietary protocols and the use of flow control for streaming protocols. See ZSE Profile Spec. r17, Figure D.38.

typedef BEGIN_PACK struct _ZclRequestTunnelResponsePayload_t ZclRequestTunnelResponsePayload_t

RequestTunnelResponse is sent by the server in response to a RequestTunnel command previously received from the client. See ZSE Profile Spec. r17, Figure D.45.

typedef BEGIN_PACK struct _ZclSeTunnelSupportedProtocol_t ZclSeTunnelSupportedProtocol_t

Type of supported protocol entry.

typedef struct _ZclSupportedTunnelProtocolsResponsePayload_t ZclSupportedTunnelProtocolsResponsePayload_t

The response contains a list of tunnel protocols supported by the device. See ZSE Profile Spec. r17, Figure D.47.

typedef BEGIN_PACK struct _ZclTunnelClosureNotificationPayload_t ZclTunnelClosureNotificationPayload_t

TunnelClosureNotification is sent by the server to indicate that a tunnel has been closed due to expiration of a CloseTunnelTimeout. See ZSE Profile Spec. r17, Figure D.49.

enum _ZCL_SeTunnelTxStatus_t

Status of data transmission. See ZSE Profile Spec. r17, Table D.64.

Enumerator:
ZCL_SE_TUNNEL_NO_SUCH_TX_STATUS 

The TransferData command contains a TunnelID of a non-existent tunnel.

ZCL_SE_TUNNEL_WRONG_DEVICE_TX_STATUS 

The TransferData command contains a TunnelID that does not match the device sending the data.

ZCL_SE_TUNNEL_DATA_OVERFLOW_TX_STATUS 

The TransferData command contains more data than indicated by the MaximumIncomingTransferSize of the receiving device.

Definition at line 524 of file zclSmartEnergyTunnelCluster.h.

enum _ZCL_SeTunnelStatus_t
Enumerator:
ZCL_SE_TUNNEL_SUCCESS_STATUS 

The tunnel has been opened and may now be used to transfer data in both directions.

ZCL_SE_TUNNEL_BUSY_STATUS 

The server is busy and cannot create a new tunnel at the moment. The client may try again after a recommended timeout of 3 minutes.

ZCL_SE_TUNNEL_NO_MORE_ID_STATUS 

The server has no more resources to setup requested tunnel. Clients should close any open tunnels before retrying.

ZCL_SE_TUNNEL_PROTOCOL_NOT_SUPPORTED 

The server does not support the protocol that has been requested in the ProtocolID parameter of the RequestTunnel command.

ZCL_SE_TUNNEL_FLOW_CONTROL_NOT_SUPPORTED 

Flow control has been requested by the client in the RequestTunnel command but cannot be provided by the server (missing resources or no support).

ZCL_SE_TUNNEL_FIRST_RESERVED_STATUS 

Should not be returned and indicates an unknown error.
